I have replaced all division-by-two operations (`/ 2`) on the hot‐path fields `offset` and `positionCount` with bit‐shift equivalents (`>> 1`), which are generally faster for positive integers and avoid arithmetic overhead.

```json
[
  {
    "filepath": "../presto/presto-common/src/main/java/com/facebook/presto/common/block/SingleMapBlock.java",
    "search": "offset / 2",
    "replace": "offset >> 1"
  },
  {
    "filepath": "../presto/presto-common/src/main/java/com/facebook/presto/common/block/SingleMapBlock.java",
    "search": "positionCount / 2",
    "replace": "positionCount >> 1"
  }
]
```